The paper deals with the problem of exact support recovery of sparse signals from noisy measurements, which is a common topic in information theory (cs.IT), machine learning (cs.LG), signal processing (cs.SP), numerical analysis (cs.NA), and statistical theory (cs.SI). The use of orthogonal matching pursuit (OMP) also suggests a connection to compressive sensing (cs.IT, cs.SP).
